en name was moderately popular in the Middle Ages (when it was used for girls as well as boys), under the influence of a 3rd-century saint who was one of the seven deacons of Rome. He was martyred in  258 . The legend is that, having been required to hand over the Church's treasures to the civil authorities, he assembled the poor and sick and presented them. For this act of Christian defiance, he was roasted to death on a gridiron. In England the name is also associated with  St Laurence of Canterbury  (  d. 619 ). A more recent influence has been the actor  Sir Laurence Olivier  (  1907–89 ).  See also  Lawrence ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":1,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Lorenzo De Lundresford was born about 1105, in Sussex, England, his father, Reginald De Lundresford, was 34 and his mother, Elianor Moreville, was 34. He married Johanna de Vere about 1136, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1168, in his hometown, at the age of 64."},"et":{"about 1105–1168":"umbes 1105–1168","1105–1168":"1105–1168","1110–Male":"1110–Surnud","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1140–1203":"1140–1203","1072–1138":"1072–1138","1073–Female":"1073–Surnud","ABT 1136":"umbes 1136","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1073":"1073","1072":"1072","1106":"1106","1138":"1138","1105":"1105","1203":"1203","1115":"1115","1168":"1168","about 1105":"umbes 1105","about 1102":"umbes 1102",",, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"fi":{"about 1105–1168":"noin 1105–1168","1105–1168":"1105–1168","1110–Male":"1110–Kuollut","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1140–1203":"1140–1203","1072–1138":"1072–1138","1073–Female":"1073–Kuollut","ABT